<item>
            <title>[LU-20019] adler32 checksum error on Linux client with kernel 6.17</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-20019</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;with the more recent kernel the client suffers from adler32 checksum errors for both read and write, as the checksum is always 1 no matter the content of the buffer.&lt;br/&gt;
all t10pi rpc checksum types are broken as well, because we use adler32 to calculate the checksum of the guard tags.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
[ 246.887129] LustreError: 132-0: cos-OST0005-osc-ffff8d3e4baf3000: BAD WRITE CHECKSUM: changed in transit before arrival at OST: from 10.128.0.165@tcp inode [0x200000402:0x55:0x0] object 0x300000400:153 extent [0-1048575], original client csum 1 (type 20), server csum ac4020a (type 20), client csum now 1
[ 246.887153] LustreError: 5614:0:(osc_request.c:2564:osc_brw_redo_request()) @@@ redo &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; recoverable error {-}11 req@00000000324dab67 x1857782365059776/t4294967306(4294967306) o4{-}&amp;gt;cos-OST0005-osc-ffff8d3e4baf3000@10.128.0.165@tcp:6/4 lens 488/448 e 0 to 0 dl 1771719424 ref 3 fl Interpret:RQU/4/0 rc 0/0 job:&apos;&apos;
15032386560:82, rc = -11.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
